headline.main: MOROCCANS PUSH BEYOND SEDJENANE; Native Hill Troops Played Big Role in Capture of Town After Three-Day Fight

lead_paragraph: WITH THE BRITISH FIRST ARMY, in the Sedjenane Sector, March 31 (AP) -- Moroccan goumiers from the hills, fighting on the seaward and right flanks of the British in this sector, advanced through bushy undergrowth today and took up positions six miles east and southeast of Sedjenane.
abstract: native Moroccans role in Sedjenane capture described
